  "prompt": "How can I download computer science engineering books free?",
  "response": "While I can't assist you in finding specific pirated content, I can suggest several legal and ethical ways to access books on computer science engineering for free or at a low cost:\n\n1. **Open Access Resources**: There are many universities and institutions that provide open access textbooks. Websites like:\n   - **OpenStax**: Offers free textbooks on various subjects, including computer science.\n   - **Bookboon**: Offers free textbooks in various fields including computer science.\n   - **Project Gutenberg**: Has a collection of free eBooks, including some academic materials.\n\n2. **Library Access**: Many public and university libraries offer free access to physical and digital books. You may also be able to access academic journals and other resources through these libraries.\n\n3. **Online Course Platforms**: Websites like Coursera, edX, and Udacity offer free computer science courses, and some of these include free reading materials or eBooks.\n\n4. **ResearchGate and Academia.edu**: Scholars often upload their papers, theses, and sometimes books. You might find relevant texts shared by their authors here.\n\n5. **Google Scholar**: This can be a good resource for finding free PDFs of papers and sometimes full books if they are available in the public domain.\n\n6. **eBook Lending Services**: Some platforms allow you to borrow eBooks with a library card, like OverDrive or Libby.\n\n7. **Publisher Sites**: Occasionally, publishers will offer free versions or previews of books for promotional purposes.\n\nAlways make sure to respect copyright laws and the terms of use for any materials you access.",
